Step 1: Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 300421.65 and Total Revenue = 863371.65.
• Thus, 300421.65 / 863371.65 ≈ 0.34804, which is about 34.80%.

Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio.
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) / (Total Current Liabilities)
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -2419019.09.
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 5515978.61.
• Thus, -2419019.09 / 5515978.61 ≈ -0.4386, which rounds to -0.44.

The final answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "34.80%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-0.44"
  }
}
